President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. These include Thomas Harker as Assistant Secretary of the Navy, Financial Management and Comptroller; Bruce Landsberg as a Member of the Transportation Safety Board; Linda A. Puchala as a member of the National Mediation Board; Kimberly A. Reed as First Vice President of the Export-Import Bank of the United States; Peter B. Robb as General Counsel of the National Labor Relations Board. President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint Jon Adler as Director of the Bureau of Justice Assistance, Department of Justice.